1
00:00:06,974 --> 00:00:09,774
[♪]

2
00:01:15,408 --> 00:01:17,141
TAWASHI:
Mars sure has come a long way

3
00:01:17,174 --> 00:01:19,008
since the last time
I was here.

4
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:22,708
MILO:
And unfortunately,
so has our crime rate.

5
00:01:35,874 --> 00:01:37,808
TAWASHI:
I'll tell you, sheriff,

6
00:01:37,841 --> 00:01:39,408
if all goes well
with our operation,

7
00:01:39,441 --> 00:01:41,141
we'll be able
to stop these crooks

8
00:01:41,174 --> 00:01:43,474
from selling their stolen robots
here for good.

9
00:01:43,508 --> 00:01:45,408
And your planet
will be much safer.

10
00:01:45,441 --> 00:01:47,908
Exactly, detective.

11
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:50,308
It's almost time
for our suspect to show up.

12
00:01:50,341 --> 00:01:52,274
TAWASHI:
I can't tell you how many times

13
00:01:52,308 --> 00:01:55,041
he's slipped past me
back on Earth.

14
00:01:55,074 --> 00:01:58,108
But I have this feeling
it's all going to
change today.

15
00:01:58,141 --> 00:01:59,174
Huh?

16
00:02:14,208 --> 00:02:15,774
Good morning.

17
00:02:15,808 --> 00:02:18,374
It's such a pleasure
to see your face again.

18
00:02:18,408 --> 00:02:20,274
I wish I could say the same.

19
00:02:20,308 --> 00:02:23,941
But all you ever do
is try to sell me
useless junk.

20
00:02:23,974 --> 00:02:26,741
TAWASHI:
That's Grunert, all right.

21
00:02:26,774 --> 00:02:28,041
Go! Go!

22
00:02:28,074 --> 00:02:29,208
Go!

23
00:02:29,241 --> 00:02:30,841
[SIRENS WAILING]

24
00:02:30,874 --> 00:02:32,074
BOTH:
Ahh!

25
00:02:34,308 --> 00:02:36,474
Ah!

26
00:02:38,874 --> 00:02:40,074
What is this?

27
00:02:40,108 --> 00:02:41,074
Hah!

28
00:02:45,908 --> 00:02:48,041
You miserable humans!

29
00:02:48,074 --> 00:02:49,474
These robots
don't belong to you.

30
00:02:49,508 --> 00:02:52,374
As of now, all of them are free.

31
00:02:52,408 --> 00:02:53,708
All of them!

32
00:02:58,341 --> 00:03:00,774
Ah! Huh?

33
00:03:02,108 --> 00:03:04,008
This is for you, Blue Knight.

34
00:03:07,108 --> 00:03:08,341
[LAUGHING WICKEDLY]

35
00:03:08,374 --> 00:03:10,308
Oh, no!

36
00:03:10,341 --> 00:03:13,741
Grunert's got a
spectral-magnetic
destabilizer!

37
00:03:13,774 --> 00:03:16,008
Always be prepared
for the worst.

38
00:03:16,041 --> 00:03:18,241
That's the rule
for surviving in space.

39
00:03:18,274 --> 00:03:19,308
Huh?

40
00:03:19,341 --> 00:03:21,241
Filthy human!

41
00:03:23,774 --> 00:03:26,041
[GRUNERT LAUGHING WICKEDLY]

42
00:03:33,308 --> 00:03:34,874
This is my lucky day.

43
00:03:36,374 --> 00:03:39,208
Was that...a memory?

44
00:03:41,441 --> 00:03:43,908
So the Blue Knight
couldn't stay away.

45
00:03:43,941 --> 00:03:46,274
Take a look
at this.

46
00:03:46,308 --> 00:03:48,808
Now he's trying
to free stolen robots.

47
00:03:51,008 --> 00:03:52,941
Yeah,
that's his style.

48
00:03:52,974 --> 00:03:54,474
But, doctor,
what are they stealing
the robots for?

49
00:03:54,508 --> 00:03:55,941
What do
they do with them?

50
00:03:55,974 --> 00:03:57,941
The robots are forced
to fight each other

51
00:03:57,974 --> 00:04:00,408
in battles called Extreme
Extermination tournaments.

52
00:04:00,441 --> 00:04:02,474
That has a bad ring to it.

53
00:04:02,508 --> 00:04:05,141
Right. They're
incredibly brutal
fights with no rules.

54
00:04:05,174 --> 00:04:06,074
Pure
entertainment.

55
00:04:06,108 --> 00:04:09,141
[GASPS]

56
00:04:09,174 --> 00:04:10,408
O'SHAY:
<i>The robots are stolen,</i>

57
00:04:10,441 --> 00:04:13,208
<i>then modified and forced to</i>
<i>fight to the finish.</i>

58
00:04:13,241 --> 00:04:15,474
<i>Most of them</i>
<i>are so badly damaged,</i>

59
00:04:15,508 --> 00:04:17,341
<i>they have to be</i>
<i>scrapped.</i>

60
00:04:17,374 --> 00:04:19,874
<i>And there's one man</i>
<i>behind it all.</i>

61
00:04:19,908 --> 00:04:22,274
<i>His name is Grunert.</i>

62
00:04:22,308 --> 00:04:24,941
ASTRO:
<i>Not him again.</i>

63
00:04:24,974 --> 00:04:27,208
Sounds like I'm gonna have to
pay him a visit.

64
00:04:27,241 --> 00:04:30,141
Well, the Blue Knight
will probably try
the same thing,

65
00:04:30,174 --> 00:04:33,174
which would explain why
he's on Mars right now.

66
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:36,808
But I'm afraid
he's going to
go too far.

67
00:04:47,908 --> 00:04:51,008
Shadow, tell me,
who am I?

68
00:04:57,541 --> 00:04:59,308
You built me,
didn't you?

69
00:04:59,341 --> 00:05:01,908
You're very
perceptive.

70
00:05:05,408 --> 00:05:07,008
TENMA:
Hmm.

71
00:05:07,041 --> 00:05:10,108
I always felt he might be
one of Shadow's creations.

72
00:05:10,141 --> 00:05:12,174
Shadow, you have to tell me

73
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:13,974
about these nightmares
I keep having.

74
00:05:14,008 --> 00:05:15,041
Where do they come from?

75
00:05:15,074 --> 00:05:16,741
[LAUGHING WICKEDLY]

76
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:20,074
They come from
who you were

77
00:05:20,108 --> 00:05:23,274
before you were reborn
as the Blue Knight.

78
00:05:23,308 --> 00:05:25,108
What do you mean, reborn?

79
00:05:25,141 --> 00:05:27,074
I made you
from another robot.

80
00:05:27,108 --> 00:05:28,774
But not
an ordinary one.

81
00:05:28,808 --> 00:05:30,474
This one had
real heart.

82
00:05:30,508 --> 00:05:33,074
It was what
I needed to make you
as strong as you are.

83
00:05:33,108 --> 00:05:35,041
His heart,
his determination,

84
00:05:35,074 --> 00:05:37,941
came from
his boundless hatred
for humans.

85
00:05:37,974 --> 00:05:39,841
Boundless hatred for humans.

86
00:05:39,874 --> 00:05:41,374
[GRUNTS]

87
00:05:52,141 --> 00:05:53,108
[LAUGHING WICKEDLY]

88
00:06:01,141 --> 00:06:02,208
It's all coming back.

89
00:06:03,408 --> 00:06:05,274
I remember.

90
00:06:05,308 --> 00:06:07,408
But I don't
understand

91
00:06:07,441 --> 00:06:09,274
why you took those
memories away from me.

92
00:06:09,308 --> 00:06:11,108
If I'd left
them in,

93
00:06:11,141 --> 00:06:14,408
all you would have
cared about was revenge
against Grunert.

94
00:06:14,441 --> 00:06:16,508
So I took
the memories away,

95
00:06:16,541 --> 00:06:19,208
but I left your emotions
in place.

96
00:06:19,241 --> 00:06:23,308
And it's been your anger
that has made you unstoppable.

97
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:26,841
Shadow, you've got to
tell me about
my past life.

98
00:06:26,874 --> 00:06:29,308
I want to know why you built me.

99
00:06:29,341 --> 00:06:31,441
Just follow your instincts,
my friend,

100
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:34,074
and everything will soon
be clear to you.

101
00:06:36,174 --> 00:06:39,141
TENMA:
Everything's already
very clear to me, Shadow.

102
00:06:39,174 --> 00:06:40,908
The Blue Knight's purpose

103
00:06:40,941 --> 00:06:43,108
is to give Astro
a glimpse of his future.

104
00:06:44,908 --> 00:06:46,274
MAN:
<i>Grunert, everyone's</i>
<i>been complaining</i>

105
00:06:46,308 --> 00:06:50,208
<i>that the Extreme Extermination</i>
<i>matches are getting boring.</i>

106
00:06:50,241 --> 00:06:51,908
It's not my fault.

107
00:06:51,941 --> 00:06:54,008
I tried to buy better robots,
but the Blue Knight--

108
00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:55,941
<i>Quiet!</i>
Ooh!

109
00:06:55,974 --> 00:06:57,441
<i>You're fired, Grunert.</i>

110
00:06:57,474 --> 00:06:59,908
Oh, please!
Don't do that!

111
00:06:59,941 --> 00:07:02,174
I'll set up the most incredible
match you've ever seen.

112
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:04,241
<i>Promises, promises, promises.</i>

113
00:07:04,274 --> 00:07:07,141
How does the Blue Knight
sound to you?

114
00:07:07,174 --> 00:07:11,174
I could make sure he's beaten
so badly, he'd be scrap metal.

115
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:12,508
<i>The Blue Knight?</i>

116
00:07:12,541 --> 00:07:14,474
<i>All right,</i>
<i>I'll give you one last chance.</i>

117
00:07:14,508 --> 00:07:17,241
<i>But you better not</i>
<i>mess this one up.</i>

118
00:07:17,274 --> 00:07:19,074
Overgrown bully.

119
00:07:19,108 --> 00:07:21,108
Someday, I'll show him.

120
00:07:21,141 --> 00:07:24,274
Now, how am I supposed to find
the Blue Knight anyway?

121
00:07:24,308 --> 00:07:27,374
It's not like I can just
look him up in the phone book.

122
00:07:27,408 --> 00:07:28,408
Boss!

123
00:07:28,441 --> 00:07:30,041
There's trouble.

124
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:31,341
One of the robots
is going crazy.

125
00:07:31,374 --> 00:07:32,174
Well, stop it!

126
00:07:37,341 --> 00:07:38,241
Thrasher?

127
00:07:42,541 --> 00:07:43,941
Huh?

128
00:07:43,974 --> 00:07:46,408
Your robot has not gone crazy.

129
00:07:46,441 --> 00:07:48,474
I have just modified him,
that is all.

130
00:07:48,508 --> 00:07:50,474
As you can see,
he's stronger now.

131
00:07:50,508 --> 00:07:53,174
He is, but who are you?

132
00:07:53,208 --> 00:07:57,008
I am your new
business partner.

133
00:08:08,508 --> 00:08:10,341
Mars is still
a frontier, Astro,

134
00:08:10,374 --> 00:08:13,308
just like the Old West
used to be.

135
00:08:13,341 --> 00:08:15,741
Yeah, especially
when it comes to bad guys.

136
00:08:15,774 --> 00:08:17,874
We have to find
Grunert, and fast.

137
00:08:17,908 --> 00:08:19,341
That's not
going to be so easy.

138
00:08:19,374 --> 00:08:21,108
Let's try
this place.

139
00:08:21,141 --> 00:08:23,441
I don't think that's
such a good idea.

140
00:08:26,108 --> 00:08:28,974
Does anyone in here
know where I can find
a man named Grunert?

141
00:08:31,008 --> 00:08:32,508
O'SHAY:
Uh, Astro,

142
00:08:32,541 --> 00:08:36,741
maybe we should be
a little more discreet
about this.

143
00:08:36,774 --> 00:08:39,408
So you wanna know
where Grunert is,
do you?

144
00:08:39,441 --> 00:08:42,074
Yes, we've been trying
to track him.

145
00:08:42,108 --> 00:08:44,074
Well, I used to
supply him
with robots,

146
00:08:44,108 --> 00:08:46,041
but then the fool
stopped buying them from me.

147
00:08:46,074 --> 00:08:47,208
Grunert's gonna be

148
00:08:47,241 --> 00:08:50,174
at Mount Olympus
today at high noon.

149
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:51,741
But you're not
the only ones

150
00:08:51,774 --> 00:08:53,274
who know about this
little appointment.

151
00:08:53,308 --> 00:08:55,774
The Blue Knight just rode outta
town, and he's headed that way.

152
00:08:55,808 --> 00:08:57,141
The Blue Knight?

153
00:08:57,174 --> 00:08:58,974
Doctor,
Grunert may get hurt!

154
00:08:59,008 --> 00:09:01,741
He must be stopped, Astro.

155
00:09:01,774 --> 00:09:03,208
Got it.

156
00:09:03,241 --> 00:09:05,241
Let's rocket!

157
00:09:19,774 --> 00:09:21,274
ASTRO:
Blue Knight!

158
00:09:24,874 --> 00:09:26,041
Listen to me.

159
00:09:26,074 --> 00:09:27,941
I know you want to save robots,

160
00:09:27,974 --> 00:09:30,008
but you can't do it
by hurting humans.

161
00:09:30,041 --> 00:09:34,808
Nobody's going to
lay a hand on them,
so cool your jets!

162
00:09:34,841 --> 00:09:39,841
Astro...you really don't
know much about human nature,
do you?

163
00:09:39,874 --> 00:09:41,941
Human nature?

164
00:09:41,974 --> 00:09:42,608
What do you mean?

165
00:09:44,474 --> 00:09:46,341
You've got a lot
to learn, kid.

166
00:09:46,374 --> 00:09:48,774
Unfortunately,
I learned the hard way.

167
00:09:48,808 --> 00:09:49,874
Listen to me, Astro.

168
00:09:58,141 --> 00:10:01,108
Crusher's getting in
some real solid blows, folks,

169
00:10:01,141 --> 00:10:03,741
but Thrasher
isn't giving up yet.

170
00:10:06,941 --> 00:10:07,941
[BELL RINGS]

171
00:10:07,974 --> 00:10:09,074
We have an upset!

172
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:11,108
Crusher's the new champ!

173
00:10:11,141 --> 00:10:13,308
BLUE KNIGHT:
<i>In the past they</i>
<i>called me Cobalt,</i>

174
00:10:13,341 --> 00:10:16,274
<i>and I was</i>
<i>a robot technician.</i>

175
00:10:16,308 --> 00:10:18,341
Cobalt, do you think
you can fix him up

176
00:10:18,374 --> 00:10:20,908
so he'll be ready
to fight tomorrow?

177
00:10:20,941 --> 00:10:22,441
It's pretty bad,
sir.

178
00:10:22,474 --> 00:10:23,908
The best I can do

179
00:10:23,941 --> 00:10:26,508
is get Thrasher
back up to 70 percent
capacity.

180
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:28,308
Well, it's good enough
for Extreme Extermination.

181
00:10:28,341 --> 00:10:30,741
But when he's at
such a low level,

182
00:10:30,774 --> 00:10:32,508
he'll never make it
through the whole match.

183
00:10:32,541 --> 00:10:34,274
He'll break down
in the middle of the ring.

184
00:10:34,308 --> 00:10:36,908
We can't disappoint
our loyal fans now.

185
00:10:36,941 --> 00:10:40,741
So if you want to keep your job,
make sure he comes out fighting.

186
00:10:40,774 --> 00:10:43,074
Very sure.

187
00:10:43,108 --> 00:10:45,074
BLUE KNIGHT:
<i>I worked hard</i>
<i>to repair the robots</i>

188
00:10:45,108 --> 00:10:47,774
<i>damaged during</i>
<i>the matches.</i>

189
00:10:47,808 --> 00:10:49,408
Hey...

190
00:10:49,441 --> 00:10:53,108
I never thought I'd end up
on this table.

191
00:10:53,141 --> 00:10:57,441
Guess it happens to all of us
sooner or later.

192
00:10:57,474 --> 00:11:00,274
Don't want to
talk to me, huh?

193
00:11:00,308 --> 00:11:04,374
Are you mad because of
all the other robots
I've wrecked?

194
00:11:04,408 --> 00:11:06,174
I'm not mad
at you.

195
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:07,408
Just sad,
that's all.

196
00:11:07,441 --> 00:11:09,274
Sad?

197
00:11:09,308 --> 00:11:12,508
I thought robots
didn't have emotions.

198
00:11:12,541 --> 00:11:14,308
BLUE KNIGHT:
<i>But I did have emotions</i>

199
00:11:14,341 --> 00:11:16,274
<i>and I was beginning</i>
<i>to hate humans</i>

200
00:11:16,308 --> 00:11:18,041
<i>because of what they did</i>
<i>to robots.</i>

201
00:11:18,074 --> 00:11:20,408
[LAUGHING WICKEDLY]

202
00:11:20,441 --> 00:11:23,808
[GRUNTS]

203
00:11:23,841 --> 00:11:25,241
GRUNERT:
Make sure he's fixed
by tomorrow.

204
00:11:25,274 --> 00:11:29,008
If he's walking and talking,
that'll be good enough.

205
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:30,408
[GRUNTS]

206
00:11:33,174 --> 00:11:35,074
BLUE KNIGHT:
<i>I worked day and night,</i>

207
00:11:35,108 --> 00:11:37,974
<i>and the more I saw,</i>
<i>the more I hated.</i>

208
00:11:42,174 --> 00:11:44,308
[GRUNTING]

209
00:11:46,174 --> 00:11:48,274
Well, you'll be okay
for now, Thrasher.

210
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:51,074
But I can't guarantee that I'll
be able to fix you next time,

211
00:11:51,108 --> 00:11:51,908
or the time
after that.

212
00:11:51,941 --> 00:11:53,474
I know.

213
00:11:53,508 --> 00:11:54,941
But I've got to do
what I'm told.

214
00:11:54,974 --> 00:11:56,508
I'm a robot.

215
00:11:56,541 --> 00:11:59,108
But do we really
have to do what we're told,

216
00:11:59,141 --> 00:12:00,808
or is it just
a choice we make?

217
00:12:00,841 --> 00:12:02,241
What if things were different?

218
00:12:02,274 --> 00:12:03,274
BLUE KNIGHT:
<i>A few days later,</i>

219
00:12:03,308 --> 00:12:05,908
<i>Grunert decided</i>
<i>to send us to Mars.</i>

220
00:12:10,508 --> 00:12:12,408
Listen up, ladies.

221
00:12:12,441 --> 00:12:14,774
We have new worlds to conquer.

222
00:12:14,808 --> 00:12:17,441
Extreme Extermination
is going to Mars.

223
00:12:17,474 --> 00:12:20,074
Cobalt, you're
gonna be working
extra hard,

224
00:12:20,108 --> 00:12:22,008
'cause there'll be
a lot more damage
to repair.

225
00:12:22,041 --> 00:12:23,741
I can't do it.

226
00:12:23,774 --> 00:12:25,241
Can't do it?

227
00:12:25,274 --> 00:12:27,508
Are you saying
it's too much
work for you?

228
00:12:27,541 --> 00:12:29,174
Then how about this.

229
00:12:29,208 --> 00:12:31,074
Do what you can
with the time
you're given,

230
00:12:31,108 --> 00:12:33,808
even if you can
only get them
up to 5 or 10 percent.

231
00:12:33,841 --> 00:12:35,408
I don't care,
as long as they can move.

232
00:12:37,108 --> 00:12:38,741
I know what I can do.

233
00:12:38,774 --> 00:12:40,008
All right.

234
00:12:43,474 --> 00:12:45,341
BLUE KNIGHT:
<i>I'd made up my mind.</i>

235
00:12:45,374 --> 00:12:49,974
<i>I was going to free the robots</i>
<i>before we got to Mars.</i>

236
00:13:00,374 --> 00:13:01,974
The emergency shuttle's
ready for us.

237
00:13:02,008 --> 00:13:03,341
CRUSHER:
I cannot believe

238
00:13:03,374 --> 00:13:04,408
someone cares enough
about us to help.

239
00:13:07,974 --> 00:13:11,174
There's more to us than steel
and wire and circuit boards.

240
00:13:11,208 --> 00:13:13,874
A lot more.

241
00:13:13,908 --> 00:13:18,074
I believe we have hearts and
souls, just like the humans do.

242
00:13:24,841 --> 00:13:26,074
Huh?

243
00:13:26,108 --> 00:13:28,774
No, you don't.

244
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:31,308
<i>And how dare you try</i>
<i>to run away?</i>

245
00:13:31,341 --> 00:13:34,274
You're my property.
I own you.

246
00:13:34,308 --> 00:13:39,274
And I can do
anything I want
to your ungrateful circuitry.

247
00:13:39,308 --> 00:13:41,241
It doesn't matter
what happens to me.

248
00:13:41,274 --> 00:13:42,808
Not really.

249
00:13:42,841 --> 00:13:45,041
But all of you will have
a choice to make someday.

250
00:13:47,008 --> 00:13:48,341
Enough with that!

251
00:13:49,774 --> 00:13:51,774
[LAUGHING]

252
00:13:51,808 --> 00:13:53,474
BLUE KNIGHT:
<i>I floated in space</i>

253
00:13:53,508 --> 00:13:57,008
<i>for a long time,</i>
<i>but I never gave up.</i>

254
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:59,108
<i>I just didn't have</i>
<i>enough energy left</i>

255
00:13:59,141 --> 00:14:01,741
<i>to get to</i>
<i>a space station.</i>

256
00:14:01,774 --> 00:14:06,041
If only I had the strength.

257
00:14:24,874 --> 00:14:26,374
SHADOW:
You want strength?

258
00:14:26,408 --> 00:14:29,141
I'll give you more
than you could imagine.

259
00:14:29,174 --> 00:14:30,808
Huh?

260
00:14:30,841 --> 00:14:31,941
Who are you?

261
00:14:31,974 --> 00:14:33,141
Why are you doing this?

262
00:14:33,174 --> 00:14:36,108
My name is Shadow.

263
00:14:36,141 --> 00:14:39,841
And I'm doing this
because I admire your spirit.

264
00:14:39,874 --> 00:14:42,808
Shadow saved my life,
and then he jacked up
my power

265
00:14:42,841 --> 00:14:44,841
and transformed me
into the Blue Knight.

266
00:14:44,874 --> 00:14:48,374
Now all I care about
is protecting robots.

267
00:14:48,408 --> 00:14:49,474
They're coming.

268
00:14:49,508 --> 00:14:50,874
[GASPS]

269
00:14:56,974 --> 00:14:58,074
Where are
the robots?

270
00:14:58,108 --> 00:14:59,941
Something's
wrong.

271
00:14:59,974 --> 00:15:01,374
The man
at the café

272
00:15:01,408 --> 00:15:03,308
said Grunert
was coming here
to buy more robots.

273
00:15:03,341 --> 00:15:04,874
But I don't see
any of--

274
00:15:04,908 --> 00:15:06,774
Arggh!

275
00:15:08,074 --> 00:15:09,241
We've been
set up.

276
00:15:09,274 --> 00:15:11,174
BLUE KNIGHT:
It's a trap.

277
00:15:12,174 --> 00:15:15,141
Ahhhhh!

278
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:22,108
Ahhhhh!

279
00:15:25,074 --> 00:15:26,408
Are you
all right?

280
00:15:26,441 --> 00:15:27,441
Yeah.

281
00:15:27,474 --> 00:15:29,041
GRUNERT:
<i>It's showtime!</i>

282
00:15:29,074 --> 00:15:31,841
<i>This is a fight</i>
<i>to the finish.</i>

283
00:15:31,874 --> 00:15:35,141
<i>Astro and the Blue Knight</i>
<i>against my robots.</i>

284
00:15:35,174 --> 00:15:36,141
<i>[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]</i>

285
00:15:37,908 --> 00:15:41,341
Someone's going to wind up
on the scrap heap.

286
00:15:41,374 --> 00:15:43,074
<i>How can he</i>
<i>do this?</i>

287
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:44,441
<i>You shouldn't</i>
<i>be surprised.</i>

288
00:15:44,474 --> 00:15:45,808
<i>It's his nature.</i>

289
00:15:45,841 --> 00:15:47,274
<i>Human nature.</i>

290
00:15:47,308 --> 00:15:49,874
I love a knock 'em,
sock 'em robot bash.

291
00:15:49,908 --> 00:15:51,974
Yeah, yeah!
Ain't it the best?

292
00:15:52,008 --> 00:15:55,974
GRUNERT:
<i>Let the match begin!</i>

293
00:15:56,008 --> 00:15:59,474
I will never raise
my sword against
a fellow robot.

294
00:15:59,508 --> 00:16:01,841
That's such a sweet sentiment,

295
00:16:01,874 --> 00:16:03,774
but you're going to fight
whether you want to or not.

296
00:16:05,774 --> 00:16:08,241
[ASTRO GRUNTING]

297
00:16:16,074 --> 00:16:17,074
[LAUGHING]

298
00:16:22,074 --> 00:16:24,441
It looks like the Blue Knight's
keeping his word.

299
00:16:24,474 --> 00:16:26,474
And we all know where
that's going to lead:

300
00:16:26,508 --> 00:16:28,141
straight to
the recycling bin.

301
00:16:28,174 --> 00:16:32,408
TENMA:
Astro, the Blue Knight
knows what he is doing.

302
00:16:32,441 --> 00:16:34,174
You're going to learn
a lot from him.

303
00:16:34,208 --> 00:16:37,208
He has the key to your future.

304
00:16:37,241 --> 00:16:38,441
Stop it!

305
00:16:38,474 --> 00:16:41,108
There's no reason
for us to be fighting.

306
00:16:42,541 --> 00:16:44,174
Forget it, Astro.

307
00:16:44,208 --> 00:16:48,474
You can't reason with them.
They're just machines.

308
00:16:48,508 --> 00:16:50,141
I'm getting sick
of that smirk.

309
00:16:50,174 --> 00:16:52,141
Blue Knight!

310
00:16:52,174 --> 00:16:53,141
[GASPS]

311
00:17:01,008 --> 00:17:02,774
I'm coming!

312
00:17:02,808 --> 00:17:03,974
Huh?

313
00:17:04,008 --> 00:17:06,041
<i>[GRUNERT LAUGHING]</i>

314
00:17:06,074 --> 00:17:06,941
<i>You're doing good, boys.</i>

315
00:17:06,974 --> 00:17:08,841
<i>Now finish the job.</i>

316
00:17:08,874 --> 00:17:09,908
<i>Crush him!</i>

317
00:17:13,241 --> 00:17:14,774
I'm not the enemy!

318
00:17:14,808 --> 00:17:16,708
I want to help!

319
00:17:21,508 --> 00:17:24,441
<i>Hey, what are</i>
<i>you stopping for?</i>

320
00:17:24,474 --> 00:17:26,308
MAN: Let's go, let's go.
MAN 2: Come on.

321
00:17:26,341 --> 00:17:27,841
MAN:
What's taking so long?

322
00:17:27,874 --> 00:17:30,241
Huh. Maybe they all had
some kind of breakdown.

323
00:17:35,108 --> 00:17:36,241
[GRUNTS]

324
00:17:40,474 --> 00:17:41,908
So now what?

325
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,874
You don't want to fight?

326
00:17:46,908 --> 00:17:48,108
I can make you.

327
00:17:48,141 --> 00:17:50,341
I'll fry your circuits
with this thing.

328
00:17:50,374 --> 00:17:52,074
[ALL GROAN IN PAIN]

329
00:17:52,108 --> 00:17:53,508
Stop it!

330
00:17:53,541 --> 00:17:55,774
You have no right
to hurt them like this.

331
00:17:55,808 --> 00:17:57,808
They're just robots.

332
00:17:57,841 --> 00:18:00,774
We're robots,
but that's not all we are.

333
00:18:00,808 --> 00:18:02,041
Huh?

334
00:18:02,074 --> 00:18:03,774
JACKAL:
We can think.

335
00:18:03,808 --> 00:18:06,741
We have emotions!

336
00:18:06,774 --> 00:18:08,274
You can't ignore us.

337
00:18:08,308 --> 00:18:11,041
We're not gonna
take it anymore.

338
00:18:11,074 --> 00:18:12,908
You're not, huh?

339
00:18:12,941 --> 00:18:15,941
Well, I think you're going to be
feeling a lot differently

340
00:18:15,974 --> 00:18:17,508
once I go up to
maximum output.

341
00:18:17,541 --> 00:18:20,208
[ALL SCREAMING]

342
00:18:20,241 --> 00:18:21,241
You've gotta
fight it.

343
00:18:25,774 --> 00:18:27,074
[YELLS]

344
00:18:29,308 --> 00:18:31,441
Crusher, Thrasher,
Jackal...

345
00:18:31,474 --> 00:18:33,474
my old friends.

346
00:18:33,508 --> 00:18:37,274
We never wanted to fight you,
but Grunert ordered us to.

347
00:18:37,308 --> 00:18:39,041
I am so sorry.

348
00:18:40,374 --> 00:18:41,474
Arggh!

349
00:18:41,508 --> 00:18:42,841
Crusher!

350
00:18:42,874 --> 00:18:43,841
ASTRO:
Grunert!

351
00:18:47,541 --> 00:18:51,508
Do not worry, Astro,
you have got him on the run.

352
00:18:51,541 --> 00:18:53,741
But soon, you will have to
make a choice.

353
00:18:56,408 --> 00:18:58,508
I'll come back.
And when I do--

354
00:18:58,541 --> 00:19:00,074
Ahh!

355
00:19:00,108 --> 00:19:01,908
You're not coming back, Grunert.

356
00:19:01,941 --> 00:19:02,741
It's over.

357
00:19:02,774 --> 00:19:04,741
Finished.

358
00:19:04,774 --> 00:19:06,774
Arggh!

359
00:19:11,208 --> 00:19:12,274
Help.

360
00:19:14,474 --> 00:19:15,374
Ugh!

361
00:19:16,841 --> 00:19:18,141
Arggh!

362
00:19:20,041 --> 00:19:21,908
Astro, it's your choice

363
00:19:21,941 --> 00:19:23,874
if you want to hang
with these heartless humans,

364
00:19:23,908 --> 00:19:26,174
but as far as I'm concerned,
they only want one thing.

365
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,274
And it's to destroy us.

366
00:19:32,208 --> 00:19:34,274
You feeling
any better now?

367
00:19:34,308 --> 00:19:37,741
I am sure I will
after you fix me
up again.

368
00:19:37,774 --> 00:19:40,241
Right. Count on it, Crusher.

369
00:19:40,274 --> 00:19:45,341
You do that, and I will
follow you wherever you go.

370
00:19:45,374 --> 00:19:47,208
Huh?

371
00:19:47,241 --> 00:19:49,741
Are you saying that you'll
fight the humans with me?

372
00:19:49,774 --> 00:19:51,241
You bet.
Of course.
Yeah.

373
00:19:56,141 --> 00:19:57,774
TENMA:
Shadow...

374
00:19:57,808 --> 00:20:01,741
that is quite an impressive
robot you have built.

375
00:20:01,774 --> 00:20:04,441
I could not have designed
a more perfect robot.

376
00:20:04,474 --> 00:20:08,341
The Blue Knight is the ideal
role model for Astro,

377
00:20:08,374 --> 00:20:12,008
<i>as he continues</i>
<i>to evolve.</i>

378
00:20:14,241 --> 00:20:17,041
Humans and robots.

379
00:20:17,074 --> 00:20:19,508
Do you think we'll ever really
understand each other?

380
00:20:19,541 --> 00:20:22,774
Hmm? Hmm.

381
00:20:22,808 --> 00:20:24,408
Uh...

382
00:20:24,441 --> 00:20:27,474
of course we'll learn to
understand each other.

383
00:20:27,508 --> 00:20:30,141
But it will
take time.

384
00:20:40,974 --> 00:20:42,708
[♪]

